Vice President Mike Pence delivered a speech at Coast Guard Base Portsmouth, thanking the men and women of the Coast Guard and the Department of Homeland Security for their service and dedication. He expressed gratitude on behalf of President Donald Trump and promised to support them in their mission to protect the American people. Pence highlighted the challenges they face, particularly along the southern border, and emphasized the need for border security. He praised the efforts of the joint task force and the partnerships with other agencies and international partners. Pence also mentioned the administration's actions to strengthen the military and provide resources for law enforcement. He concluded by expressing his admiration and appreciation for the sacrifices made by the Coast Guard and DHS personnel, and assured them that the American people are grateful for their service.